A grade 12 pupil of Phandulwazi Agriculturalultural High School boarding school in Alice must attend classes with a broken jaws, damage to her facial bone structure and an injured left eye after her teacher allegedly ran over her head in his three-ton flat-bed truck. Zintle Magwa, 19, is in severe pain and has a swollen face that keeps her up all night, according to said her mother, Bulelwa Magwa, 49.&nbsp;For the full story get a copy of the Dispatch or subscribe to our e-Edition for the complete newspaper with jobs, classifieds, crosswords, TV schedules and back editions.